						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab built into a step of the Hanumān temple near the Veṅkaṭēśvara temple.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription records a grant of land in <hi rend="bold">Ṟaṭehaḷi-sīme</hi> by a person (name lost) of the <hi rend="bold">Jōyisa</hi> family. He belonged to the <hi rend="bold">Āśvalyana</hi>-<hi rend="italic">sūtra</hi>-<hi rend="bold">Maduveya</hi>-<hi rend="italic">suṁka</hi> (marriage tax) is mentioned.</p>						

						<p>The characters belong to about the <hi rend="bold">15th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
